n%^BOLD%^-=%^RESET%^%^MAGENTA%^Fate Domain%^BOLD%^%^WHITE%^=-%^RESET%^

The fate domain deals with luck of all types, and as such is shared by very different deities. Each of the spells involved has a random component that is determined by fate itself.

Clerics with the Fate Domain gain the following benefits:
- A chance to add 1d4 to a normally failed saving throw.

The fate domain contains the following spells:

True Strike, Auspicious Bolt, Precognitive Perception, Aegis Of Fate, Fortune Fate

%^CYAN%^Deities%^RESET%^: Kismet, Lysara

%^BOLD%^Please see individual help files for an explanation of what each spell does.%^RESET%^
